# AlphaVision Equity Terminal — environment variable template
#
# Usage:
#   cp .env.template .env
#   Fill in your actual values in .env
#   Never commit .env to source control (it is listed in .gitignore)
#
# All variables below are optional. The application runs without them
# but with reduced data accuracy as described in each section.
#
# See docs/providers.md for the full fallback chain and signal impact.

# ── Analyst Signals (Finnhub) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Used for:
#   - Rating Drift score: net analyst upgrades minus downgrades (last 30 days)
#   - Consensus Strength score: Strong Buy + Buy fraction
#   - Upside Gap score: analyst consensus mean price target
#
# Without this key:
#   The application falls back to yfinance analyst data. yfinance provides
#   monthly recommendation snapshots and price targets but lacks the
#   upgrade/downgrade event stream. Scores remain valid but Rating Drift
#   will reflect monthly counts rather than individual event timestamps.
#
# Get a free key at: https://finnhub.io/
# Free tier: 60 API calls / minute — sufficient for ~520-ticker weekly runs.

FINNHUB_API_KEY=your_finnhub_api_key_here

# ── Fundamentals (SEC EDGAR) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Used for:
#   - Rule of 40: revenue growth YoY % + FCF margin %
#   - Earnings Quality: free cash flow / net income
#
# Without a custom identity:
#   The application uses the generic default identity
#   "AlphaVision Research research@alphavision.local". SEC EDGAR still
#   works but rate limits are tighter for anonymous/generic identities.
#   Set a real name and email to get better throughput and comply with
#   the SEC Fair Access policy: https://www.sec.gov/os/accessing-edgar-data
#
# Format: "Full Name email@yourdomain.com"

EDGAR_IDENTITY=Your Name your.email@example.com

# ── Azure Blob Storage (optional, for weekly DB backup) ─────────────────────
#
# Used for:
#   - Uploading the SQLite weekly report database to Azure Blob Storage
#
# Without this:
#   The database backup step is skipped. Analysis results are only
#   stored locally in the SQLite file.
#
# Get a connection string from the Azure portal under your Storage Account
# → Access keys → Connection string.

AZURE_STORAGE_CONNECTION_STRING=DefaultEndpointsProtocol=https;AccountName=...
